{
 "name": "RPlog_Waking_Up",
 "title": "Waking Up: An Interrogation in a Rotting Cell",
 "summary": "Two captives--the Mon Calamari Senator Tokoga and the medic Myiari Oerstead--wake from drugged sleep in a decaying, hidden cell, watched by the Imperial intelligence officer Rainer and the stormtrooper Brek. Rainer demands Tokoga's access codes to the New Republic Defense Council's master mainframe, threatening to torture the shell-shocked, panic-stricken Myiari to break him. As the Senator defiantly refuses, Brek is ordered to manhandle and beat the terrified medic, who lashes out violently between bouts of hysteria, even as a flicker of reluctance shows beneath the trooper's faceless helmet. Rainer escalates with a slaver's shock prod and a slow blaster-melt threat aimed at Tokoga, until Myiari--unable to watch another death--breaks and offers to slice into the system herself in exchange for sparing the Senator. Rainer accepts, knocks Tokoga out, and has Brek haul the Senator off to the computer room to ensure the medic has 'proper motivation' to cooperate.",
